      "writtenOn": "2017-04-06T19:06:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s SIGSYS:\n\nfrom man 7 signal:\n\n(Where three values are given, the first one is usu‐\n       ally valid for alpha and sparc, the middle one for x86, arm, and most other architectures, and the last one for mips.\n\nSIGUSR2   31,12,17\nSIGSYS      12,31,12\n\nSo I think 31 is SIGSYS on the platforms that we likely care the most about... but this mismatch also suggests we should keep 31 instead of matching an individual signal name.",
      "parentUuid": "ebc3da67_360eaf98",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 19
      },
